(33, 1, '2020-04-23 10:16:13', '2020-04-23 10:16:13', '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The SWAG Toolkit is a collection of lesson plans designed to support Black men in improving their overall well-being, whether directly via community member-oriented holistic sexuality education, or indirectly via provider-oriented competency training. We were guided by their voices and their needs and included authors from the community or with extensive experience working in the community.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>“Swag” is a word used to describe how a person presents themselves to the world, with confidence and sophistication and in a way that earns respect and credibility. Our goal has been to provide Black gay and bisexual men with sexual health resources that empower them and support them holistically so they can be confident in making decisions about their sexual health.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"align\":\"center\",\"id\":27,\"sizeSlug\":\"large\",\"className\":\"toolkit-button\"} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-image toolkit-button\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-large\"><img src=\"http://swagtoolkit.test/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/icon-toolkit.svg\" alt=\"Toolkit\" class=\"wp-image-27\"/></figure></div>\n<!-- /wp:image -->', 'Relevant sex education materials for Black gay and bisexual men', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '2-revision-v1', '', '', '2020-04-23 10:16:13', '2020-04-23 10:16:13', '', 2, 'http://swagtoolkit.test/2020/04/23/2-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(34, 1, '2020-04-27 07:35:30', '2020-04-27 07:35:30', '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The SWAG Toolkit’s name was inspired by the men who helped us build it. “Swag” is a word used to describe how a person presents themselves to the world, with confidence and sophistication and in a way that earns respect and credibility. &nbsp;From the start, we wanted to provide Black gay and bisexual men with tools and resources that empower them to be confident when it comes to their sexual health and relationships.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The toolkit includes materials for community-oriented holistic sexuality education programming and materials for training healthcare providers who serve Black men.  As we designed the toolkit, we engaged the community and their voices guided us in listening sessions, focus groups, interviews, and pilot sessions.  We hope you enjoy the tools even more than we enjoyed developing them!</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"align\":\"center\",\"id\":27,\"sizeSlug\":\"large\",\"className\":\"toolkit-button\"} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-image toolkit-button\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-large\"><img src=\"http://swagtoolkit.test/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/icon-toolkit.svg\" alt=\"Toolkit\" class=\"wp-image-27\"/></figure></div>\n<!-- /wp:image -->', 'Relevant sex education materials for Black gay and bisexual men', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '2-revision-v1', '', '', '2020-04-27 07:35:30', '2020-04-27 07:35:30', '', 2, 'http://swagtoolkit.test/2020/04/27/2-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
